fields.description:
A customer mentions instances launched by cloud-formation stack fails to add tags to instances occasionally.   I have tested it in internal prc cloud, but could not reproduce it. The same thing was working in earlier euca versions (4.3)

Here is the stack file which customer used to launch instances.

{code}
{

"AWSTemplateFormatVersion": "2010-09-09",

"Description": "ASG tagging check",

"Resources" : {

"MyLaunchConfig" : {

"Type" : "AWS::AutoScaling::LaunchConfiguration",

"Properties" : {

"ImageId" : "emi-6ae0c7a4",

"InstanceType" : "m1.small",

"KeyName" : "KEYNAMEHERE",

"SecurityGroups" : [ "default" ]

}

},

"MyASG" : {

"Type" : "AWS::AutoScaling::AutoScalingGroup",

"Properties" : {

"LaunchConfigurationName" : { "Ref" : "MyLaunchConfig" },

"AvailabilityZones" : { "Fn::GetAZs" : "" },

"Tags": [

{ "Key": "test:tag:1", "Value": "testvalueA", "PropagateAtLaunch": "true" },

{ "Key": "test:tag:2", "Value": "testvalueB", "PropagateAtLaunch": "true" },

{ "Key": "test:tag:3", "Value": "testvalueC", "PropagateAtLaunch": "true" },

{ "Key": "test:tag:4", "Value": "testvalueD", "PropagateAtLaunch": "true" }

],

"MinSize" : 4,

"MaxSize" : 4

}

}

}

}
{code}

Customer confirmed that, it is happening occasionally.

comments.body:
Customer has asked for hot-fix patch file as it is heavily affecting their development team.

Here is what customer says in zendesk :

{code}
We have some large development teams that are using tags in their automated environments heavily so it's effecting use cases with hundreds of instances.

Depending on the fix, we most likely need a hot fix to implement it.
{code}

[~kshaik], please check if the autoscaling group has the expected tags. This will help narrow down if the issue occurs with cloudformation or with autoscaling:

{code}
# euscale-describe-tags | grep MYGROUPNAME
{code}

the above command must be run as the admin user for the account that owns the group (called MYGROUPNAME in the example)

Is there any error logging on the cloud controller when the issue occurs? this may help identify the cause of the problem.

[~sjones], as you suggested in earlier update, customer had tried to create auto-scaling group with min/max/desired capacity of zero and all instances got the tags correctly when he increased the values to 2 for all stacks. He executed a total of 10 stacks with same fashion, all the stacks got tags to the instances.  He followed same fashion and ran it thrice.   In all those attempts, instances got created with tags.

Now customer came back with a different question.  Here is customer query.

{code}
From implementation perspective it doesn't make sense that the template would actually start the template resource (AWS::AutoScaling::AutoScalingGroup) before all the settings have been applied to it. Is the same approach used for other resource types as well, what settings might other resources miss occasionally?
{code}
